<h1>Ember Accordion</h1>
<p>
  An Ember addon which provides components for creating a list of items with collapsible content panels.
</p>

<h2>Classic Behavior</h2>
<p>
  The simplest use case of {{#code-inline}}component:accordion-list{{/code-inline}} behaves much like a classic
  accordion from <a href="getbootstrap.com/2.3.2/javascript.html#collapse">boostrap</a> or
  <a href="https://jqueryui.com/accordion/">jQuery UI</a> where clicking on an item opens
  a panel and <i>closes other sibling items</i>.
</p>

<h2>Enhanced Behaviors</h2>
<p>
  The {{#code-inline}}component:accordion-list{{/code-inline}} also supports some enhanced
  behavior:
  <ul>
    <li>Configure whether multiple items can be open at once</li>
    <li>Set default open panel(s)</li>
    <li>Provide multiple toggle/panel pairs per item</li>
    <li>Components rendered in the panel have access to a close action</li>
    <li>Accordions are easily nestable</li>
  </ul>
</p>
